main_text: पंजाब में किसान गेहूं की नाड में आग लगा रहे हैं जिससे आए दिन हादसे ही रहे हैं। 15 मई की शाम डेराबसी के गांव दफ़रपुर में किसान ने गेहूं की कटाई के बाद बचे अवशेषों में आग लगा दी। आग इतनी भयंकर थी जो शामलात में बनी मजदूरों की झुग्गियों तक पहुंच गई। इस आग में डेढ़ साल की बच्ची जिंदा जल गई। जिस किसान ने खेतों में आग लगाई थी पुलिस ने उसे गिरफ्तार कर लिया है। पंजाब में खेतों में आग लगाने के कारण पहले भी हादसे हो चुके हैं । कुछ दिन पहले गुरदासपुर के गांव बिजलीवाल में भी खेतों में लगी आग के कारण स्कूल बस चपेट में आ गई थी। 2 बच्चे उस हादसे में घायल हुए थे। लेकिन इन हादसों के बाद न तो किसान सबक ले रहे हैं और न ही प्रशासन ऐसे किसानों पर कार्रवाई कर रहा है।#theforefrontnews #theforefront #wheat #agriculture #stubbleburning #dangerous #deathofakid #derabassi #punjab #punjabnews #punjabgovernment ________________________________________We are also available atTelegram: https://t.me/theforefront22Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC3eh06j4XpCKtQ-T0SI_gqATwitter: https://twitter.com/forefront_theFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/theforefront2022

comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "maggiemetz"  "comment_text": "My heart has been broken for the people of Ukraine.
My people.

I am proud to be half Ukrainian. 🇺🇦🤍

My grandfather escaped to America when he was young. He sought freedom and a better life for his family. And here I am 70+ years later reaping the benefits of his selfless pursuit.

I am free  my children are free  and the homeland from which my ancestors came—and where some are still living—is a place worthy of escape even today.

Life is heavy.
The world is broken.
My heart hurts.

Will you pray with me for the people of Ukraine?
My people.

For safety  comfort  justice  mercy  and peace.

On behalf of the beautiful people of Ukraine  let us pray.

-MM

comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "nishmakespizza"  "comment_text": "75% whole wheat.

Formula:
* 360g levain (80% hydration)
* 710g @bartonspringsmill Rouge de Bourdeaux
* 90g @kingarthurbaking Sir Galahad
* 660g water
* 21g salt
* 1.75g instant yeast

Method:
* Bake @ 400f with steam for 20 mins
* Remove steam  vent  bake for another 30 mins to internal temp of 205f
* Remove from pans  bake for another 5 mins to create crust

Yield: two loaves (5x9)

Adapted from @maurizio and @kenforkish

main_text: I grew some wheat over the winter indoors in a bucket of recycled soil I found on the side of the road by sewing bird seed into it by accident.So I am growing more of it indoors and outdoors.By the looks of the world right now growing your own wheat is probably going to become a pretty popular past time; especially once we run out of gas completely or summer temperatures kill too many people to sustain society or the machinery breaks down.We took the wrong technology path and now we are becoming useless digital zombies.Given how automation of jobs has gone in the past I also dont expect some robot slave utopia where money is obsolete and we all live happy lives with all the time in the world for VR porn.So if I become one of the 100s of millions of roaming homeless I can at least find a remote location to start a stealth farm on Crown Land.#wheat #society #civilization #gardening #meditations #endoftheworldtour
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "reflectionfrequency"  "comment_text": "I grew some wheat over the winter indoors in a bucket of recycled soil I found on the side of the road by sewing bird seed into it by accident.

So I am growing more of it indoors and outdoors.

We took the wrong technology path and now we are becoming useless digital zombies.

Given how automation of jobs has gone in the past I also dont expect some robot slave utopia where money is obsolete and we all live happy lives with all the time in the world for VR porn.

So if I become one of the 100s of millions of roaming homeless I can at least find a remote location to start a stealth farm on Crown Land.

#wheat #society #civilization #gardening #meditations #endoftheworldtour"}}

main_text: P L A N T I N G 🌱 S E A S O NSpring is planting season around the farm and with all this gorgeous weather we’ve been busy!Different fields need different treatment depending on the crops to be grown soil health etc. Some of the steps that need to be taken may include spreading composted manure (we sure do stink up the neighbourhood for a few days every spring 💩) tilling the land planting some seeds (such as corn 🌽 beans grains etc.) and/or fertilizing winter crops.Here you can see a spreader full of fertilizer about to be applied to a nearby field of winter wheat 🌾 Dad says it will help the wheat grow big and chunky just like me.- Roscoe 🐾#dairy #dairyfarm #dairyfarmersofcanada #dairyfarmersofontario #cows #cowsofinstagram #twincreekfarm #TCF #holstein #agriculture #wheat #fertilizer #tractor #caseih #farmdog #dogsofinstagram #ontario #canada #farm #farming #spring #canadianfarmers #milk #cheese #canadiandairy #support #supportfarmers #photography
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "twincreekfarmdairy"  "comment_text": "P L A N T I N G 🌱 S E A S O N

Spring is planting season around the farm  and with all this gorgeous weather  we’ve been busy!

Different fields need different treatment depending on the crops to be grown  soil health  etc. Some of the steps that need to be taken may include spreading composted manure (we sure do stink up the neighbourhood for a few days every spring 💩)  tilling the land  planting some seeds (such as corn 🌽  beans  grains  etc.) and/or fertilizing winter crops.

Here you can see a spreader full of fertilizer  about to be applied to a nearby field of winter wheat 🌾 Dad says it will help the wheat grow big and chunky  just like me.
- Roscoe 🐾
